DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0304-4076(91)90091-Q
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/030440769190091Q
AB  - The method developed in this paper deviates from the main approaches of thecost-of-living literature. We argue that, from the perspective of the econometrician, we would like to choose a system of demands which best fits the data. However, this may require estimating a demand system for which the underlying utility function is not known or a demand system for which compensated income cannot easily be computed. We demonstrate applicability of Vartia's (1983) algorithm for calculating a Konüs cost-of-living index for a demand system that previously could not be used in applied welfare work due to these deficiencies.
ER  - 

